# Release Notes: v3.0.0

We are excited to announce version 3.0 of the platform. This is a major release with new features, performance improvements, and breaking changes.

!> This release contains **breaking changes**. Please read the migration guide carefully.

## New Features

### Real-Time Collaboration

Multiple users can now edit documents simultaneously with live cursor tracking and conflict resolution.

### Advanced Search

Full-text search with support for:

- Boolean operators (`AND`, `OR`, `NOT`)
- Phrase matching with `"exact phrase"`
- Field-specific queries with `field:value`
- Wildcard patterns with `*`

### Export Improvements

New export formats:

| Format | Description |
| --- | --- |
| PDF | High-fidelity PDF with embedded fonts |
| EPUB | E-book format for mobile readers |
| LaTeX | For academic publishing |
| Docx | Microsoft Word compatible |

## Performance

- Page load time reduced by **40%**
- Search queries now complete in under $50ms$ (p99)
- Memory usage reduced by **25%** through lazy loading

## Breaking Changes

W> The following changes require updates to your configuration.

### API Changes

1. The `/api/v2/` endpoints are now deprecated
2. Authentication switched from API keys to OAuth 2.0
3. Rate limits reduced from 1000 to 600 requests per minute

### Configuration

The configuration file format changed from TOML to YAML:

```yaml
server:
  port: 8080
  host: 0.0.0.0
database:
  url: postgres://localhost/mydb
  pool_size: 20
```

Previously:

```toml
[server]
port = 8080
host = "0.0.0.0"

[database]
url = "postgres://localhost/mydb"
pool_size = 20
```

## Migration Guide

- [ ] Update API client to use OAuth 2.0
- [ ] Convert configuration files from TOML to YAML
- [ ] Update API endpoints from v2 to v3
- [ ] Test all integrations against the new API
- [ ] Review rate limiting changes

T> Run the migration script at `scripts/migrate-v3.sh` to automate most of the configuration changes.
